text.tspan: The server must stand behind the baseline and
serve the ball into the opponent's service box
on the other side of the net.
The serve must be made underhand or
overhand, and it must land in the opposite
service box diagonally across from the server.
The server gets two chances to get the serve in,
and if they fail to do so on both attempts, it's
called a double fault, and the point is awarded
If the set is tied at 6-6, a tiebreaker is played to
In a tiebreaker, the first player to win seven points
with a lead of at least two points wins the set.
To win a game, a player must win two points in a
row from deuce. This is called advantage.
To win a set, a player must win six games, with a
lead of at least two games.
